A road has 349 houses on it numbered from 1 to 349.
The diagram shows some of these houses.
The houses on the West side of the road have odd numbers.
The houses on the East side have even numbers.

\begin{InsertScreenShot}
    %\relincludegraphics{Figures/Q04-Houses.png}
\end{InsertScreenShot}

\begin{parts}
\item Put a ring around the numbers in this list that are on the West side.

\begin{center}
25 \quad 87 \quad 126 \quad 178 \quad 252 \quad 329
\end{center}
\Marks{1}

\item On the East side, how many houses are there between the house numbered 168 and the house numbered 184?

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\item How many houses on the road have a house number that is a multiple of 39?

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}

\item Tomaz delivers a leaflet to every house on the West side of the road.
He starts at house number 1 and then delivers to each house in order.

\begin{subparts}
\item Find an expression, in terms of $n$, for the house number of the $n$th house he delivers to.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}

\item Work out the house number of the 40th house he delivers to.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{1}

\item Work out how many houses are on the West side of the road.

\AnswerLine[][]
\Marks{2}
\end{subparts}

\item Alicia delivers a leaflet to every house on the East side of the road.
She starts at house number 348 and then delivers to each house in order.

\begin{subparts}
\item Find an expression, in terms of $n$, for the house number of the $n$th house she delivers to.

